{"word":"εὐκταῖος","slug":"εὐκταῖος","sections":[{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":""},{"paragraph":"<el><b>εὐκταῖος</b></el> <el>(εὐκταῖος, η, ον) </el><br/><b><a href='S:Etymology'>Etym.</a> </b><a href='S:εὔχομαι'><el>εὔχομαι</el></a>\n<p/><div class='li750'><b>1. </b><i>of</i> or <i>for prayer, votive</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Aristophanes'>Ar.</a></b>: <i>devoted</i>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b>:— <el>εὐκταῖα, τά</el>, <i>votive offerings, vows, prayers</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Sophocles'>Soph.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>2. </b>of gods, <i>invoked by prayer</i>, <b><a href='S:Aeschylus'>Aesch.</a></b>, <b><a href='S:Euripides'>Eur.</a></b><p/></div><div class='li750'><b>3. </b><i>prayed for</i>, <b><a href='S:Anthology'>Anth.</a></b><p/></div>"}]}